<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 7: VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN
        BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - OIL PICK-UP TUBE
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>OIL PICK-UP TUBE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
            <title>REMOVAL</title>
            <para>Perform the following steps:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With pulley damper removed, remove the oil pick-up tube as follows: (Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600763">7.63</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ) (Rear sump tube shown).
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the two (2) retaining bolts at the front cover.</para>
                    <figure id="ef1600761" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5070" filename="../figeg5/eg5070.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 7.61 Removing Vibration Damper</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1600762" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5075" filename="../figeg5/eg5075.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 7.62 Removing Front Engine Mounting Bracket</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1600763" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg5297" filename="../figeg5/eg5297.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 7.63 Removing Oil Pick-up Tube</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Support oil pick-up tube and remove retaining bolt at support bracket (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk document="e160_195.xml" xrefid="ef1600764">7.64</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ).
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the pick-up tube and gasket. Discard gasket.</para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>Remove piston and connecting rod assemblies as described in Section 6.</para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
